  "description": "Chief Petty Officer 1st Class Tom Riefesel, MMM, CD joined the Royal Canadian Navy on 22 December 1982 as a Signalman Sea 261. In September 1983, he joined his first ship, HMCS Assiniboine. Over the length of his career, he progressed from Signalman, to Yeoman Signals, Combat Chief, Chief Yeoman of Signals NATO Standing Naval Force Atlantic, Chief Naval Communicator at Sea Training Atlantic. CPO1 Riefesel served on 8 different destroyers, frigates and AORs, HMCS Assiniboine, HMCS Ottawa, HMCS Protecteur, [&#8230;]",
  "content:encoded": "<p>Chief Petty Officer 1st Class Tom Riefesel, <a title=\"Order of Military Merit (Canada)\" href=\"http://www.cmp-cpm.forces.gc.ca/dhr-ddhr/chc-tdh/chart-tableau-eng.asp?ref=MMM\">MMM</a>, <a title=\"Canadian Forces' Decoration (CD)\" href=\"http://www.cmp-cpm.forces.gc.ca/dhr-ddhr/chc-tdh/chart-tableau-eng.asp?ref=CD\">CD</a> joined the <a title=\"Royal Canadian Navy\" href=\"http://www.navy-marine.forces.gc.ca/en/index.page\" target=\"_blank\">Royal Canadian Navy</a> on 22 December 1982 as a Signalman Sea 261.</p>\n<p>In September 1983, he joined his first ship, <a title=\"HMCS Assiniboine\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMCS_Assiniboine_(DDH_234)\" target=\"_blank\">HMCS Assiniboine</a>. Over the length of his career, he progressed from Signalman, to Yeoman Signals, Combat Chief, Chief Yeoman of Signals <a title=\"NATO Standing Naval Force Atlantic\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standing_NATO_Maritime_Group_1\" target=\"_blank\">NATO Standing Naval Force Atlantic</a>, Chief Naval Communicator at Sea Training Atlantic. CPO1 Riefesel served on 8 different <a title=\"Destroyers\" href=\"http://www.navy-marine.forces.gc.ca/en/fleet-units/destroyers-home.page?\" target=\"_blank\">destroyers</a>, <a title=\"Frigates\" href=\"http://www.navy-marine.forces.gc.ca/en/fleet-units/frigates-home.page?\" target=\"_blank\">frigates</a> and <a title=\"Canadian Supply Ships\" href=\"http://www.navy-marine.forces.gc.ca/en/fleet-units/supply-home.page?\" target=\"_blank\">AORs</a>, HMCS Assiniboine, <a title=\"HMCS Ottawa\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMCS_Ottawa_(DDH_229)\" target=\"_blank\">HMCS Ottawa</a>, <a title=\"HMCS Protecteur\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMCS_Protecteur_(AOR_509)\" target=\"_blank\">HMCS Protecteur</a>, <a title=\"HMCS Margaree\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMCS_Margaree_(DDH_230)\" target=\"_blank\">HMCS Margaree</a>, <a title=\"HMCS Preserver\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMCS_Preserver_(AOR_510)\" target=\"_blank\">HMCS Preserver</a>, <a title=\"HMCS Athabaskan\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMCS_Athabaskan_(DDG_282)\" target=\"_blank\">HMCS Athabaskan</a>, <a title=\"HMCS Iroquois\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMCS_Iroquois_(DDG_280)\" target=\"_blank\">HMCS Iroquois</a>, <a title=\"HMCS Toronto\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMCS_Toronto_(FFH_333)\" target=\"_blank\">HMCS Toronto</a> and <a title=\"HMCS Ville de Québec\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMCS_Ville_de_Qu%C3%A9bec_(FFH_332)\" target=\"_blank\">HMCS Ville de Québec</a> from the<a title=\"Maritime Forces Atlantic\" href=\"http://www.navy-marine.forces.gc.ca/en/about/structure-marlant-home.page?\" target=\"_blank\"> Atlantic Fleet</a>, and shore establishments such as the <a title=\"Maritime Command Headquarters\" href=\"http://www.mc.nato.int/Pages/home.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Maritime Command Headquarters</a>, Canadian Forces Language School Shearwater, and the Canadian Naval Operation School.</p>\n<p>Promoted Chief Petty Officer 1st class in February 2005, CPO1 Riefesel immediately joined and served with Maritime Force Atlantic Headquarters N6 as the Unit Chief and was appointed Coxswain of HMCS Ville de Québec in June 2006. On completion of his tour in 2008 he was appointed as Coxswain for Sea Training Atlantic where he remained until July 2009.</p>\n<p>In July 2009, he was appointed as the Formation Chief Petty Officer for Maritime Forces Atlantic, a position he held until his current appointment as Chief Petty Officer of the Navy in August 2012.</p>\n<p>You can follow the Royal Canadian Navy Bravo Zulu of the week on Twitter at #RCNBZoftheweek and CPO1 Riefesel @RCNCPO</p>\n<p>Follow me on Twitter @MikeLacroix32</p>\n<p>You can support this site by shopping on <a title=\"Amazon.ca\" href=\"http://www.amazon.ca?_encoding=UTF8&tag=thecanamilihi-20\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>.  You still enjoy Amazon&#8217;s great prices, but a portion of your purchase goes to supporting the show.</p>\n<p><audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-668-30\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/CMHP-Episode-029-CPO1-Tom-Riefesel.mp3?_=30\" /><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/CMHP-Episode-029-CPO1-Tom-Riefesel.mp3\">http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/CMHP-Episode-029-CPO1-Tom-Riefesel.mp3</a></audio><br />\n<a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-686\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-6-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"photo (6)\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-6-300x199.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-6.jpg 460w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>On 29 June 2010, the Royal Canadian Navy celebrated its 100th anniversary&#8230;</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-685\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-7-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"photo (7)\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-7-300x200.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-7.jpg 1023w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>&#8230; and marched with the National Colours of the Royal Canadian Navy.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-5.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-687\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-5-300x224.jpg\" alt=\"photo (5)\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-5-300x224.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-5-1024x764.jpg 1024w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-5.jpg 1296w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>CPO1 Riefesel hosts the Senior Chief Petty Officers of the Pacific Fleet.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-688\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-4-192x300.jpg\" alt=\"photo (4)\" width=\"192\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-4-192x300.jpg 192w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-4.jpg 544w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 192px) 100vw, 192px\" /></a></p>\n<p>CPO1 Riefesel, MMM, CD and Vice-Admiral Mark Norman, CMM, CD visit with Vice-Admiral (Ret&#8217;d) Ralph Hennessey, DSC, CD, the oldest living Vice-Admiral of the Royal Canadian Navy.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-8.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-684\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-8-296x300.jpg\" alt=\"photo (8)\" width=\"296\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-8-296x300.jpg 296w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-8.jpg 806w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 296px) 100vw, 296px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Chief Petty Officer First Class Tom Riefesel receives his Medal of Military Merit from the Governor General.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-691\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-1-300x194.jpg\" alt=\"photo (1)\" width=\"300\" height=\"194\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-1-300x194.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-1.jpg 470w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Tom calls this his &#8216;Office&#8217;!  CPO1 Riefesel is the Cox&#8217;n of HMCS Ville de Quebéc.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-689\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-3-300x219.jpg\" alt=\"photo (3)\" width=\"300\" height=\"219\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-3-300x219.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-3.jpg 477w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The Ensign of the Royal Canadian Navy.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-683\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-2-287x300.jpg\" alt=\"photo 2\" width=\"287\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-2-287x300.jpg 287w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-2-980x1024.jpg 980w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-2.jpg 1358w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 287px) 100vw, 287px\" /></a></p>\n<p>CPO1 Riefesel and the former Chief Petty Officers of the Royal Canadian Navy.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-21.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-690\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-21-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"photo (2)\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-21-300x225.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-21-1024x768.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Tom staying fit on land.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/msm-2013.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-671\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/msm-2013-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"MSD\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/msm-2013-300x200.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/msm-2013-1024x682.jpg 1024w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/msm-2013.jpg 1800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>CPO1 Riefesel and the Commander of the Royal Canadian Navy, Vice-Admiral Mark Norman attends the presentation of the Meritorious Service Medals (Military Division) to seven members of the Royal Canadian Navy and an Honorary Navy Captain from His Excellency the Right Honourable David Johnston, Governor General and Commander-in-Chief of Canada, September 12, 2013 at Rideau Hall.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/13906459403_0e08e818f61.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-669\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/13906459403_0e08e818f61-240x300.jpg\" alt=\"13906459403_0e08e818f6[1]\" width=\"240\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/13906459403_0e08e818f61-240x300.jpg 240w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/13906459403_0e08e818f61.jpg 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 240px) 100vw, 240px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Chief Petty Officer 1st Class Tom Riefesel, Command Chief of the Royal Canadian Navy addresses HMCS Trentonian&#8217;s veterans during the launch of White Ensign Flying.  On 12 April, 2014 the Chief stressed to the crowd the RCN today has been built on the strength of the veterans and the actions and sacrifices they made.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-682\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"photo\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo-300x225.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/photo.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>CPO1 Riefesel meets with the veterans of HMCS Trentonian.</p>\n",
